Fun shoot today with @averyswail @katiekeough_ @marielaileen 

I know nothing about styling but Mariel made Katie look awesome while Avery and I took some pics 👌🏼

Tested out the new 14mm GM and 35mm GM on the Alpha 1 from @sonyalpha such a good combo, may have to retire the 16-35 🙈

Big thanks to @averyswail for putting this together 🙌🏼

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Braedin Toth - Vancouver📍 in Bella Coola, British Columbia with @jasmine.lorimer, @sonyalpha, @visitbellacoola, and @greatbearsailingadventures. May be an image of lake and nature.

node.text:
On another episode of “amazing things to do in Bella Coola that I didn’t think were possible” .. our group literally woke up, had coffee and took a sailboat to a secluded hot spring.

What resonated the most from this day was how functional and fun sailing can be.

We had a sailing legend named Pete (aka Captain Insanity) from @greatbearsailingadventures take us out, cook us a crab breakfast from some traps he dropped previously, and brought us to some hot springs for a couple hours.

I overloaded Pete with questions about how things work and what adventures he’s taken and because of those conversations, I have already joined a waiting list for a sailing club near my house in White Rock 😂

While everyone was packing up I took a few quick portraits on my @sonyalpha a7siii with my go-to “do everything lens” the 16-35mm GM.

I love wide portraits to emphasize the locations we visit. The ocean view, sailboat and mountains behind Jasmine is a great reminder of how epic that day was.

I had the new 35mm 1.4 GM lens on preorder but unfortunately it was delivered while I was on my trip. That will be my go-to portrait lens for the foreseeable future.

Will definitely be going back here 👌🏼 #alphacollective #bealpha

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Braedin Toth - Vancouver📍 on June 20, 2021 tagging @explorecanada, @hellobc, @immarcoo, @djiglobal, @canada, @tothmedia, @visitbellacoola, and @tweedsmuirair. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
One of the best days of my life.

A few days ago we strapped our wood canoe to a float plane and explored some icebergs..

When Bobby from @firvale_wilderness_camp said he knows a guy who can make this happen I honestly didn’t thing it was possible.

That’s because we didn’t know there was a nice family owned business called @tweedsmuirair who are absolute legends and made it all happen.

We arrived and strapped the canoe to the side of a beautiful 1949 Beaver with over 40k hours on it and flew to the mountains.

If you ever decide to @visitbellacoola this is one of the best experiences along the way.

I’ll continue sharing experiences from Bella Coola over the next week or so as I go through photos and videos. So much more to come!

Spent the last few days at the amazing @firvale_wilderness_camp while in Bella Coola, BC.

@visitbellacoola has so many gems I can’t wait to start editing some of the footage!

Since BC is now open for travel I highly recommend Bella Coola. We’ve been horseback riding, sailing, climbing, rafting, and there is potential that we may be strapping our wood canoe to a float plane (tbd).. 

I only have positive things to say about this magical place. Thanks to Jen & Bobby for being incredible hosts!

#explorebc #visitbellacoola

node.text:
Contrary to popular belief the no-seat option is actually quite a vibe 👌🏼

One of the canoe seats got crushed when a transmission tipped over in my back seat coming back from Vancouver island.

Despite being wrapped in a tarp it also leaked tranny fluid all over my carpet which now smells toxic/kind of good.

I was in a rush to catch the ferry back home and should have just moved my bed and clothes and put it in the truck bed so lesson learned 🙈 at least @immarcoo can shift into second gear now 👌🏼

node.text:
Here’s a 5 second burst of 50mp raw photos from the new @sonyalpha A1 camera.

I still haven’t figured out all the nuances of shooting 30fps and turning it into a video file but man oh man the dynamic range and noise reduction is crazy.

This was shot using the 16-35mm GM mounted vertically on the @djiglobal RS2 gimbal and used a remote trigger for the burst.

Iso 25600, f2.8, and 1/250 shutter (shutter needs to be higher than the usually 1/50th for 30fps to work.

You end up with an 8.6k raw file, this one was 4GB after turning it into prores 4444 xq (7GB of raws).

If you have any questions or recommendations on what to shoot let me know 👌🏼

With @jasmine.lorimer @e.s.r.j and Ben at his beautiful @bctreehouse ✨

#alphacollective #bealpha
